-- Boston Red Sox Owner Aims to Remove All Acquisition Debt From Liverpool
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2010-10-06T16:54:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/boston-red-sox-owner-aims-to-remove-all-acquisition-debt-from-liverpool.html
New England Sports Ventures, owner of
baseball’s Boston Red Sox, confirmed it agreed on a deal to buy
England’s Liverpool soccer team and said it wants to give the
club the resources to build for the future.  It wants to remove all acquisition debt, it said in a
statement, and “ultimately return Liverpool FC to its rightful
place in English and European football, successfully competing
for and winning trophies.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  